license: MIT

abstract: >
  We present a framework-grounded comparative evaluation (analysis plan committed to GitHub before data collection) of two LLM-based
  simulated-learner prompting protocols (Teachable Agent and Student Simulation) against two
  baselines, across 4 LLM families, 2 tutoring datasets, and 4,800 generated dialogues with
  double-blind human coding. Results show protocol-level differences are stable across model
  families and datasets, and provide practitioners with a use-case decision framework.

